{
  "texts": [
    "ChatGPT is the latest addition in this series that additionally uses dialog-based instructional data in the supervised and RL-based meta-training stages.",
    "ChatGPT has shown the ability to perform numerous tasks, and can outperform GPT-3.",
    "However, strong zero-shot performance across a wide range of tasks still does not help it achieve optimum performance on IR tasks.The comparative experimental analysis reported in Table 3 suggests that SparTerm and EPIC (based on BM25) deliver the worst performance and are inferior to SPLADE, which illustrates the importance of utilizing sparse representations.",
    "DeepImpact followed by a ColBERT re-ranker is more effective, where this underlines the importance of using independent term-based weighting.",
    "BERT-based Query ExpansionDocument ranking in IR is primarily dependent on the appropriate understanding of the query terms to retrieve the relevant documents."
  ]
}